Two lawyers and another person have on Wednesday been charged for obstruction and inciting members of the public against police officers on duty in Kisumu. Gilbery Oguso, Amos Okumu and Joseph Otieno were arrested on Tuesday night at Obanga junction, Kisumu East district for inciting an attack on police patrolling the area.According to the charge sheet, the three told the police, "We will tell these people to beat you up, burn your vehicle", as members of the public threw stones and bottles at the officers.The three are also accused of willfully obstructing the officers using a motor vehicle, forcing them to stop while on duty.They were released on a Sh100,000 bond each.The case will be mentioned on December 14, while a hearing has been scheduled for February 2, 2017.